&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Gateshead Health NHS Foundation Trust &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Queen Elizabeth Hospital&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Division of Nursing and Midwifery&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Macmillan Cancer Care Co-ordinator&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Permanent Contract Part Time 20 Hours&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Band 4 (AFC)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen to work within the acute oncology team as a Macmillan Cancer Care Co-ordinator. We are looking for a highly motivated, enthusiastic and caring individual to work within cancer care. The role has been developed in order to provide holistic needs assessments to cancer patients, working primarily with the acute oncology team but also with other cancer specialist teams within the hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The acute oncology service provides specialist support to patients requiring urgent care due to complications of their cancer or treatment. This role will appropriately support the nursing team and patients throughout their pathway ensuring timely management.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is therefore essential that you possess excellent communication, organisational and IT skills as well as having a good understanding of patient centred care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post offers an exciting opportunity to support the senior nursing team within the acute oncology service that will not only impact on the quality of patient care but will be challenging and rewarding on a personal level.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is supported through Macmillan Partnership working. For further information please contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Claire Pounder, Acute Oncology Nurse Consultant&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;(0191) 4455751 or (0191) 482000 Bleep 3160 or Email: claire.pounder1@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please note that the provisional date for interview is 23&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;rd &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;November 2020 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
